p: The enantioselective analysis was carried out on a 30% diethyl- tert-butyldimethylsilyl- Î²-cyclodextrin in a PS-086 capillary column. A total of nine chiral components were identified, eight of them were monoterpenoids and one a sesquiterpene hydrocarbon. None of the detected chiral compounds were enantiomerically pure. The results of the enantioselective analysis are reported in Table 2 and in Figure 1.
